It's connected to your apartment.

242
00:51:44,720 --> 00:51:46,915
It reaches every room
through some open pipes.

243
00:51:47,080 --> 00:51:48,718
When you talk into it...

244
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:50,757
...your voice is amplified.

245
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:54,469
This is an old building
and it's full of strange secrets.

246
00:51:57,560 --> 00:51:59,551
Listen, do you want to come in?

247
00:51:59,880 --> 00:52:01,871
Okay, but only for a minute.

248
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:10,994
No, don't close it. Someone will
come to let me know I got a phone call.

249
00:52:11,160 --> 00:52:14,072
My name is Elise Stallone Van Adler.

250
00:52:14,240 --> 00:52:17,152
I've been living here
alone for over five years.

251
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:19,788
My husband is always away for work.

252
00:52:19,960 --> 00:52:22,269
I can't go with him, because...

253
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:23,998
...I'm sick.

254
00:52:38,640 --> 00:52:42,076
It's very strange.
Rose knew I'd be arriving.

255
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:44,358
I was sure she'd be here
waiting for me.

256
00:52:44,520 --> 00:52:46,909
I don't understand where she could be.

257
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:50,152
Listen, what kind of people live here?

258
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:52,470
There aren't many tenants.

259
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,676
Part of the building is empty.

260
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:58,476
No, I mean...

261
00:52:58,640 --> 00:53:01,518
...anybody special. I don't know...

262
00:53:01,680 --> 00:53:04,194
I can't explain it, but
in one of her letters Rose mentioned...

263
00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:08,717
All I know is that this building used
to belong to an eccentric, rich old man.

264
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:11,030
When he died, it was vacant for years...

265
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:13,077
...until a holding company took it over.

266
00:53:14,200 --> 00:53:15,553
Who is Kazanian?

267
00:53:15,720 --> 00:53:18,917
He's an antique book seller
who has a store nearby.

268
00:53:19,080 --> 00:53:21,753
Rose bought some very
rare books from him.

269
00:53:21,920 --> 00:53:23,399
And also...

270
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:30,868
Please excuse me.

271
00:53:31,040 --> 00:53:33,110
You have a phone call,
Madame Countess.

272
00:53:33,280 --> 00:53:35,077
All right, I'll be right there.

273
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:37,754
- Bye, see you tomorrow, Mark.
- Bye.

274
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:48,873
Did you hurt yourself,
Madame Countess?

275
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:51,873
No, no, it's paint, not blood.

276
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,238
Who's there?

277
00:55:47,160 --> 00:55:48,673
Who's there?

278
00:56:01,440 --> 00:56:02,714
You filthy animal.

279
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:09,874
Damn cats.

280
00:56:20,040 --> 00:56:21,917
How much was the dose this time?

281
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:25,556
The first was 200 milligrams.

282
00:56:26,160 --> 00:56:28,720
The second, 400.

283
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:32,360
This is the strongest dose.

284
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:35,629
Do you want me to run you a bath?

285
00:56:36,800 --> 00:56:38,518
Thank you.

286
00:57:29,080 --> 00:57:30,593
Blood.

287
00:57:41,560 --> 00:57:43,710
Your bath is ready, ma'am.

288
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:46,440
Good night.
See you tomorrow morning.

289
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:48,069
Good night.

290
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:50,276
I hope you sleep well.

291
00:58:17,520 --> 00:58:19,192
There is some blood in the hallway.

292
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:21,555
Did you notice that
the door handle is broken?

293
00:58:21,720 --> 00:58:23,870
- Yes, I saw that.
- I want to tell you something.

294
00:58:24,920 --> 00:58:27,514
I thought Rose was just raving.

295
00:58:27,680 --> 00:58:31,150
Her nervousness, her fear of death...

296
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:33,669
...the myth of the Three Mothers.

297
00:58:33,840 --> 00:58:36,308
- And what's that?
- It's her obsession.

298
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:37,993
They are three Latin names.

299
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:40,595
Mater Suspiriorum...

300
00:58:40,920 --> 00:58:42,478
...the mother of sighs.

301
00:58:42,640 --> 00:58:46,030
Mater Lacrimarum, the mother of tears.

302
00:58:46,200 --> 00:58:49,431
And Mater Tenebrarum,
the mother of darkness.

303
00:58:49,600 --> 00:58:52,194
Rose read about
this myth in an old book.

304
00:58:52,360 --> 00:58:54,555
And she talks about it
like it's a true story.

305
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:57,754
She thinks someone
lives in this building.

306
00:58:57,920 --> 00:58:59,512
But I don't know.
I can't explain it to you.

307
00:58:59,680 --> 00:59:02,911
She should tell you.
It all sounds absurd to me...

308
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:05,594
...so impossible.
She's convinced that somehow...

309
00:59:05,760 --> 00:59:08,194
...the building is connected
to those three mothers.

310
00:59:08,360 --> 00:59:11,238
She talked about an architect,
Marelli or Varelli, I don't remember.

311
00:59:11,400 --> 00:59:12,435
An Italian name.

312
00:59:12,640 --> 00:59:15,712
That's how she expresses herself.
It's confusing...

313
00:59:16,040 --> 00:59:20,318
Excited. And the feeling
of always being watched.

314
00:59:20,480 --> 00:59:23,233
She's felt its presence.

315
00:59:25,240 --> 00:59:28,710
I believe her doctor gave...

316
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:37,554
Did you hear this laugh?

317
00:59:38,000 --> 00:59:39,718
- Which laugh?
- I thought I heard...

318
00:59:40,800 --> 00:59:42,313
...someone laughing.

319
00:59:42,480 --> 00:59:44,596
You were right, Elise.

320
00:59:45,480 --> 00:59:48,040
This is really blood. Come take a look.

321
00:59:59,040 --> 01:00:03,238
- Where does that door lead to?
- The service stairs. No one uses them.

322
01:00:03,480 --> 01:00:05,835
Maybe Rose went out this way.

323
01:00:06,000 --> 01:00:09,037
- I'll go take a look. You want to go?
- No, I'll wait for you here.

324
01:00:09,200 --> 01:00:11,111
I'm scared.

325
01:00:11,680 --> 01:00:13,272
All right.

326
01:02:02,240 --> 01:02:03,559
Mark.

327
01:02:04,240 --> 01:02:05,639
Mark.

328
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,188
Mark.

329
01:02:10,360 --> 01:02:12,112
Where are you?

330
01:02:34,000 --> 01:02:35,399
Mark?

331
01:02:35,800 --> 01:02:37,791
Answer me.

332
01:03:40,880 --> 01:03:43,314
Open the door, please!

333
01:05:41,000 --> 01:05:42,592
My heart.

334
01:05:44,120 --> 01:05:48,477
Please help me. Pain... My heart...

335
01:05:50,920 --> 01:05:53,798
He says it's his heart.

336
01:05:55,040 --> 01:05:57,110
A cardiotonic.
He'll feel better right away.

337
01:06:02,120 --> 01:06:03,792
My... My God.

338
01:06:03,960 --> 01:06:05,632
I'm in so much pain.

339
01:06:05,800 --> 01:06:08,792
Come on, drink this.
You'll see, it will help.

340
01:06:15,240 --> 01:06:17,754
Where did Rose go?

341
01:06:18,040 --> 01:06:19,951
Where did she go?

342
01:06:20,120 --> 01:06:22,190
Why isn't she coming back? Why?

343
01:06:23,440 --> 01:06:26,671
I think we better take him
to his apartment.

344
01:06:28,080 --> 01:06:29,195
Where did she go?

345
01:07:59,440 --> 01:08:00,589
Elise?

346
01:08:01,600 --> 01:08:03,716
Elise, it's Mark. Can you hear me?

347
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:07,118
Elise, it's Mark.

348
01:08:07,560 --> 01:08:08,709
Elise.

349
01:08:12,120 --> 01:08:14,190
Elise, it's Mark.

350
01:08:21,680 --> 01:08:23,033
It's really disgusting.

351
01:08:23,200 --> 01:08:24,918
There must be a dozen cats here.

352
01:08:25,080 --> 01:08:27,230
They keep getting in my way.

353
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:31,313
The other night one of those damn cats
scratched me and broke a little statue.

354
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:35,075
This is the last time I tell you,
because next time...

355
01:08:35,240 --> 01:08:36,719
...I'll go to the police...

356
01:08:36,880 --> 01:08:38,871
...or to the Health Department,
if I have to.

357
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:40,268
I warned you.

358
01:08:40,440 --> 01:08:42,317
You better make those...

359
01:08:42,480 --> 01:08:43,674
...damn cats disappear.

360
01:08:43,840 --> 01:08:46,832
Do whatever you want, Mr. Kazanian.

361
01:08:47,800 --> 01:08:49,074
Good morning.

362
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:51,399
Do you feel better, Mr. Elliot?

363
01:08:51,560 --> 01:08:53,596
Yes, but I don't remember
what happened to me last night.

364
01:08:53,760 --> 01:08:55,478
You weren't feeling well.
You know, your heart.

365
01:08:55,640 --> 01:08:56,834
I've never had heart problems.

366
01:08:57,000 --> 01:08:59,560
- We gave you some medicine.
- Who was that man?

367
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:01,233
That guy? His name is Kazanian.

368
01:09:01,400 --> 01:09:04,392
- He's an antique dealer.
- Thanks, and thanks for last night.

369
01:09:04,560 --> 01:09:06,152
You're welcome.

370
01:09:07,600 --> 01:09:09,511
- Mr. Kazanian.
- Yes?

371
01:09:09,680 --> 01:09:11,671
My name is Mark Elliot.
I'm Rose's brother.

372
01:09:11,840 --> 01:09:13,478
- I know you know her.
- Oh, I remember her.

373
01:09:13,640 --> 01:09:15,676
- Yes, she bought several books.
- Do you know her well?

374
01:09:15,840 --> 01:09:18,513
- No, why?
- No one has seen her in two days.

375
01:09:18,680 --> 01:09:20,910
- I thought that...
- I just sold her some books.

376
01:09:21,080 --> 01:09:22,638
What kind of books?

377
01:09:22,800 --> 01:09:25,519
Antique books, old editions.

378
01:09:25,680 --> 01:09:29,719
If you can't find her, why don't
you try the usual routine?

379
01:09:29,880 --> 01:09:32,997
- And what's that?
- Call the hospitals...

380
01:09:33,160 --> 01:09:35,913
...or the police.
- I did, but they don't know anything.

381
01:09:36,080 --> 01:09:37,911
Listen, do you understand this phrase?

382
01:09:38,080 --> 01:09:40,150
"The key is under
the sole of your shoes. "

383
01:09:40,320 --> 01:09:42,231
What's that, a riddle?

384
01:09:42,400 --> 01:09:45,358
I'm not too good with riddles.

385
01:09:49,160 --> 01:09:51,116
How long have you been here?

386
01:09:51,280 --> 01:09:54,078
I just got here yesterday.

387
01:09:54,640 --> 01:09:58,838
You know what? There is going
to be a lunar eclipse tonight.

388
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:01,560
Oh, I didn't know.

389
01:10:01,720 --> 01:10:06,396
It's been 46 years since the last
total eclipse we saw from here.

390
01:10:06,560 --> 01:10:10,109
They just said so on television.

391
01:10:10,280 --> 01:10:12,077
I urge you to watch it.

392
01:10:12,240 --> 01:10:15,949
- It will be very interesting.
- All right, I'll watch it.

393
01:10:16,160 --> 01:10:18,310
You'll thank me for it.

394
01:10:28,400 --> 01:10:31,597
Goodbye, Mr. Elliot.

395
01:10:32,160 --> 01:10:34,116
Goodbye.

396
01:11:01,360 --> 01:11:03,396
Where are you?

397
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:07,836
There you are.

398
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:11,917
There you are.

399
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:18,556
Come on, boy, come out of there.

400
01:11:21,360 --> 01:11:25,353
Come on, come out of there. Come on.

401
01:11:26,000 --> 01:11:28,355
Come here, boy.

402
01:11:30,800 --> 01:11:32,950
Good boy.

403
01:11:38,560 --> 01:11:41,154
You wanted to hide, huh?

404
01:15:14,560 --> 01:15:17,233
My crutch.

405
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:21,116
Help me!

406
01:15:32,840 --> 01:15:35,718
My legs. Help me.

407
01:15:50,080 --> 01:15:51,718
Help me!

408
01:15:58,200 --> 01:16:01,192
Please! Please!

409
01:16:06,720 --> 01:16:10,759
Oh, God! Mice, no.

410
01:16:17,680 --> 01:16:19,830
I can't take it anymore!

411
01:16:20,360 --> 01:16:23,955
Mice! Oh, my God, mice!

412
01:16:36,600 --> 01:16:38,033
Help!

413
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:53,593
Help! Oh, my God!

414
01:17:13,560 --> 01:17:16,836
Save me, Christ!
Someone get me out of here!

415
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:20,788
Get out of here! Go away!

416
01:17:21,000 --> 01:17:23,070
Please, help!

417
01:17:26,080 --> 01:17:29,197
Hurry! Hurry, run!
They're eating me alive!

418
01:17:32,440 --> 01:17:36,877
I can't take it anymore! Hurry!

419
01:17:37,160 --> 01:17:41,278
Mice! Run! Help!

420
01:18:28,200 --> 01:18:29,599
Come take a look.

421
01:18:30,040 --> 01:18:32,679
Oh, my God. That's a lot of stuff.

422
01:18:32,840 --> 01:18:37,356
That horrible countess thought
she had hidden them well.

423
01:18:37,520 --> 01:18:41,115
But you know what? It took
me less than 15 minutes to find them.

424
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:43,555
- You've been drinking today.
- No, that's not true.

425
01:18:43,720 --> 01:18:47,349
- You have been drinking, I can smell it.
- I told you I haven't.

426
01:18:53,640 --> 01:18:55,153
Well.

427
01:18:56,440 --> 01:18:59,193
Now, go upstairs and
call her husband right away.

428
01:18:59,360 --> 01:19:01,316
Do you know where to find him?

429
01:19:01,480 --> 01:19:04,233
Tell him the countess left suddenly...

430
01:19:04,400 --> 01:19:06,675
...taking all her valuables with her.

431
01:19:07,200 --> 01:19:09,589
- And what if she comes back?
- She won't.

432
01:19:10,440 --> 01:19:13,750
- Don't worry, she's never coming back.
- How can you be so sure?

433
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:15,194
What if she shows up?

434
01:19:15,400 --> 01:19:18,756
I told you, the countess
is never coming back here.

435
01:19:18,920 --> 01:19:22,230
Now, go call her husband.

436
01:19:23,280 --> 01:19:25,919
Soon, it will be our turn to enjoy life...

437
01:19:26,080 --> 01:19:28,548
...as much as the countess enjoyed it...

438
01:19:28,720 --> 01:19:31,075
...along with
all those other rich bastards.

439
01:20:06,720 --> 01:20:08,199
Who is it?

440
01:20:32,840 --> 01:20:34,398
Who's there?

441
01:20:53,960 --> 01:20:55,598
John?

442
01:21:01,400 --> 01:21:02,753
John?

443
01:21:05,640 --> 01:21:07,153
John?

444
01:23:59,560 --> 01:24:01,835
How did that phrase go?

445
01:24:04,440 --> 01:24:08,035
"Under the sole of your shoes. "

446
01:24:42,320 --> 01:24:46,438
"The key is under the sole
of your shoes. "

447
01:32:50,440 --> 01:32:52,158
Did you find the way?

448
01:32:56,440 --> 01:33:00,194
- I suppose you know who I am.
- No, I don't know.

449
01:33:00,360 --> 01:33:03,989
Many years ago, when I lived
in London, I was known as Varelli.

450
01:33:04,200 --> 01:33:08,478
Now, I use another
name in order to be forgotten.

451
01:33:08,640 --> 01:33:10,870
Are you surprised to hear my voice?

452
01:33:11,040 --> 01:33:13,474
I can only talk with this.

453
01:33:13,920 --> 01:33:16,480
I built the houses of
the Three Mothers.

454
01:33:16,640 --> 01:33:18,790
Houses that are eyes
with which they see.

455
01:33:19,000 --> 01:33:22,072
And then I buried myself in here.

456
01:33:22,240 --> 01:33:25,994
This building has become my body,
its bricks are my cells.

457
01:33:26,160 --> 01:33:28,549
Its passageways are my veins.

458
01:33:28,760 --> 01:33:31,274
Its horror is my life now.

459
01:33:32,080 --> 01:33:34,833
My sister. Where is my sister?

460
01:33:35,000 --> 01:33:38,356
Come closer. She mustn't hear us.

461
01:33:38,520 --> 01:33:41,034
She's the cruelest of all three.

462
01:33:41,200 --> 01:33:43,555
The mother of darkness.

463
01:33:44,640 --> 01:33:46,710
Come here.

464
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:52,388
You're not afraid of
an old man who can't move, are you?

465
01:33:52,600 --> 01:33:56,639
I'll whisper it in your ear.
Come a little closer.

466
01:35:06,960 --> 01:35:09,633
L... I am dying.

467
01:35:09,800 --> 01:35:11,950
But nothing will ever be able to change.

468
01:35:12,120 --> 01:35:16,750
They won't allow it.
They don't want anything to change.

469
01:35:17,440 --> 01:35:21,353
I am not the master. I am only...

470
01:35:21,520 --> 01:35:25,115
...a servant.
- Who lives in these damned houses?

471
01:35:25,280 --> 01:35:28,397
Someone who waits.

472
01:35:28,600 --> 01:35:32,229
- Who is it?
- She's watching you right now.

473
01:35:35,640 --> 01:35:37,471
But remember one thing:

474
01:35:37,680 --> 01:35:41,036
You are dust compared to her.

475
01:36:42,760 --> 01:36:44,637
Burning.

476
01:36:46,400 --> 01:36:50,712
Everything is burning.
It has already happened once before.

477
01:36:51,640 --> 01:36:53,631
We have to get out of this place.

478
01:37:16,720 --> 01:37:18,676
You will not leave.

479
01:37:19,480 --> 01:37:21,357
The end of your journey is near.

480
01:37:21,560 --> 01:37:23,516
Everything around you will become dark.

481
01:37:23,680 --> 01:37:26,797
Someone will guide you
by the hand, and you'll be glad.

482
01:37:27,000 --> 01:37:32,393
You must not be afraid. You will also
know moments of incredible light.

483
01:37:41,360 --> 01:37:45,353
You think this is magic? No.

484
01:37:45,760 --> 01:37:48,513
I am not a magician. Let's hurry now...

485
01:37:48,720 --> 01:37:52,713
...because you still have to go through
several apparitions and tremble.

486
01:37:52,920 --> 01:37:55,639
You were looking for me, right?
Just like your sister.

487
01:37:55,800 --> 01:37:58,997
This is what you wanted, right?
I'm coming to get you now.

488
01:37:59,200 --> 01:38:02,556
- Who are you?
- The Three Mothers.

489
01:38:02,720 --> 01:38:04,870
What, you don't understand?

490
01:38:05,040 --> 01:38:08,430
Mater Tenebrarum, Mater Lacrimarum...

491
01:38:09,160 --> 01:38:11,594
...Mater Suspiriorum...

492
01:38:11,760 --> 01:38:15,070
...but men call us by one name...

493
01:38:15,240 --> 01:38:17,754
...a name which frightens everyone.

494
01:38:17,960 --> 01:38:21,077
They call us Death.

495
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:22,719
Death!

496
01:39:37,200 --> 01:39:39,236
Stand back, stand back.

497
01:39:39,400 --> 01:39:40,594
Stand back.

